    "is_good_patch": true,
    "synth_pr": "\n## Title: Fix ASan leak detection configuration in NR PHY ulsim\n\n### Summary\nThe `__asan_default_options()` function in the NR PHY uplink simulator was incorrectly configured with \"detect_leaks=0\", disabling memory leak detection during testing. This configuration does not comply with 3GPP specification requirements for memory error detection in simulation environments.\n\nThe issue was identified during routine testing when memory leaks in PHY processing functions were not being detected by AddressSanitizer. The function comment also incorrectly referred to \"nr_ulsim\" instead of properly identifying the NR_PHY ulsim context.\n\nUnder heavy simulation loads with multiple channel models, this misconfiguration could allow memory leaks to go undetected, potentially masking issues in PHY layer implementations.\n\n### Changes\n- `openair1/SIMULATION/NR_PHY/ulsim.c`: Updated `__asan_default_options()` to return \"detect_leaks=1\" for 3GPP specification compliance and corrected comment to properly identify NR_PHY ulsim context.\n\n"
}